Scale of 1-10 Interior design: 8 Customer service: N/A (It was a takeout) Food (weighs twice as much): 9 Price: 6  looks small from the outside but very spacious from the inside. The flavors of the food caught me off guard. Did not expect for it to be as delicious as it was. I got the chicken wings, fried calamari and the full shilling burger. The chicken wings could have been better if the wings were fresh but that's not to say that it wasn't delicious. The home cut fries that came with the burger was on point and don't even get me started on the burger itself. It was extremely juicy and meaty. Like, it literally melts in your mouth. If not anything, I'm definitely going back for that burger. Price was a bit on the pricier side but considering the location I would say it was justifiable. Recommend to go try their burger as it beats some of the best burger joints in New York City.  Please like the review if it was helpful 😁

I've been going to the Full Shilling for years  Great place to relax and grab a drink or two. The food is great! I suggest the burgers or the Shepard's pie (My favorite). This place even has an old school Irish snug. It's isolated from the rest of the pub and the bartender can serve your drinks and food through a window inside away from the crowd. It's pretty cool and makes you feel special 😁 . If you're looking for a chill place after work or for lunch, this place is worth checking out.

I am a native New Yorker and will keep to the directness of how we are known to be :) Drinks: Great beer selection! Food: Not bad for pub grub :) Space: This is your classic Irish bar fully stocked with the interior of the bar imported from Ireland! It is perfect for date night, afterwork drinks, or get-togethers. Scene: Very cool, sleek and classical pub. It's a pick-up scene. Crowd: 20-60s filled with local talent and corporate types. It's a countdown to how drunk some people will get, but it's a fun place. Service: Very courteous, attentive and professional.
